{"id":37351,"date":"2021-11-10T11:32:40","date_gmt":"2021-11-10T07:32:40","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=37351"},"modified":"2021-11-10T11:32:40","modified_gmt":"2021-11-10T07:32:40","slug":"malik-fitnah-bidah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/11\/10\/malik-fitnah-bidah\/","title":{"rendered":"Malik on Bid\u2019ah: What is worse than contradicting the Messenger?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Muhammad ibn al-Dahhak reported: A man came to Malik ibn Anas, may Allah have mercy on him, and he said, \u201cWhere should I put on my clothes for pilgrimage?\u201d Malik said, \u201cAt the places designated by the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him.\u201d The man said, \u201cI will do it from a further place.\u201d Malik said, \u201cI do not agree with that.\u201d The man said, \u201cWhat do you dislike about that?\u201d Malik said, \u201cI dislike for you to be put to trial.\u201d The man said, \u201cWhat trial is there in doing more good?\u201d Malik said, \u201cAllah Almighty says, \u2018<strong>So let them beware who contradict his order lest they be struck by a trial or a painful punishment<\/strong>,\u2019 (24:63) and what trial is greater than that you assign a deed for yourself that was not chosen by the Messenger of Allah?\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Ba\u0304&#8217;ith &#8216;ala\u0301 Inka\u0304r al-Bida&#8217; wal-H\u0323awa\u0304dith 1\/21<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064f\u062d\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0651\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0636\u064e\u0651\u062d\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0643 \u0623\u064e\u0646 \u0631\u062c\u0644\u0627 \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0649 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0643 \u0628\u0646 \u0623\u0646\u0633 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0645\u0646 \u0623\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646 \u0627\u062d\u0631\u0645 \u0641\u0